# Performance & Optimization

## Code Splitting

Use `React.lazy()` + `Suspense` for heavy components or route-level splitting:

```typescript
import React, { Suspense, lazy } from 'react';
import Loader from 'shared/ui/Loader';

const HeavyChart = lazy(() => import('widgets/Chart/ui/Chart'));

const MyPage: React.FC = () => (
  <Suspense fallback={<Loader />}>
    <HeavyChart />
  </Suspense>
);
```

## No Barrel Files at Segment Level

**CRITICAL**: Barrel files that aggregate multiple modules break tree-shaking.

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T
// widgets/index.ts
export * from './Header';
export * from './Footer';

// ✅ DO — import directly
import Header from 'widgets/Header/ui/Header';
import Footer from 'widgets/Footer/ui/Footer';
```

## MobX Computed Values

Use `computed` for derived data — MobX caches results:

```typescript
makeObservable(this, {
  filteredProjects: computed,
});

get filteredProjects(): Project[] {
  return this._projects.filter(p => p.title.includes(this._filter));
}
```

## Image Optimization

Use native `<img>` with `loading="lazy"` for off-screen images:

```tsx
<img src={heroBg} alt="hero" loading="lazy" />
```

For critical above-the-fold images, omit `loading="lazy"`.

## DON'T

- Don't create segment-level barrels — they prevent tree-shaking
- Don't run expensive computations in render — move to MobX `computed`
- Don't import heavy libraries at the top level — use lazy imports
